olive oil
2 potato
1 sachet Brown Mustard Seeds
2 radish
1 cucumber
1 packet Masala Paste
½ tsp honey
1 tsp plain flour
1 packet chicken breast strips
1 packet panko breadcrumbs
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 packet garlic aioli

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into wedges.
• Place wedges on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle with
brown mustard seeds, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

Little cooks: Kids can help toss the wedges.

• Thinly slice radish and cucumber.
• In a medium bowl, combine masala paste, the honey, plain flour and a pinch of salt. Add chicken breast strips and toss to coat.
• In a shallow bowl, add panko breadcrumbs and Mumbai spice blend.
• Coat chicken in the seasoned panko, in batches, pressing to coat. Transfer to a plate.

• When the wedges have 10 minutes remaining, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with enough olive oil to cover the base.
• Cook crumbed chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded). Season to taste. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.

• In a second medium bowl, combine radish, cucumber, mixed salad leaves and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.
• Divide crumbed tandoori chicken, wedges and cucumber salad between plates.
• Serve with garlic aioli. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Help combine the ingredients for the salad!